"n.挑战，违抗，反抗 【英】 n. 违抗,反抗(open disobedience) 【考】 反义词：veneration( 尊敬) 【例】 The protesters showed theirdefiance of the official ban on demonstrations. n. (公然对敌对力量或政权的)反抗; 藐视(故意表示轻视) 【记】defy(vt 公然反抗; 藐视; 挑衅) 【参】defiant(adj 挑战的; 挑衅的; 目中无人的) 【反】veneration(n 尊敬; 崇拜) 【记】源自defy； de + fight 反过来打→反抗 defiance (n.)  c.1300, from Old French desfiance ""challenge, declaration of war,"" from desfiant, present participle of desfier (see defy)."
